<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>afternoon tea&nbsp;&#8212;
<br>
each ant takes away
<br>
a granule of light
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Lorin Ford
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM3></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>along the roadside
<br>
Dixie cups
<br>
of summer wind . . .
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Michael McClintock
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM5></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>upon a foreign shore
<br>
the Esperanto
<br>
of the waves
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Jim Kacian
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM7></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>North star
<br>
so many places
<br>
to call home
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Giselle Maya
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<A NAME=POEM9></A>
<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><TD><P><FONT SIZE=+1>distant galaxies . . .
<br>
taking another
<br>
wrong turn
</FONT></TD></TR> <TR ALIGN=RIGHT VALIGN=TOP><TD>
Bill Kenney
<P>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
